.TH aqsis 1 "2004" "Aqsis Version @VERSION@"
.SH NAME
aqsis - a free-as-in-freedom RenderMan engine

.SH DESCRIPTION
Aqsis is a free-as-in-freedom 3D render engine for GNU/Linux and Win32, that
conforms to the industry-standard RenderMan Interface.  Aqsis is capable of
producing motion-picture-quality output and implements all major features of
the RenderMan standard, including programmable shaders.
.PP
.RI "Please visit " "http://www.aqsis.com" " for more information."

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B aqsis [options] [RIB file ...]

.SH OPTIONS
.B -h, --help
.RS
Print help information and exit.
.RE

.B --version
.RS
Print program version information and exit.
.RE

.B --pause
.RS
Wait for a keypress after rendering is complete.
.RE

.B --progress
.RS
Print progress information while rendering (see --progressformat)
.RE

.B --Progress
.RS
Print prman-compatible progress information while rendering (same as --progressformat="R90000%p%%").
.RE

.B --progressformat=[string]
.RS
Specify a printf-style format string that overrides the default --progress output format (does not affect --Progress).  Formatting codes are: "%p" = percent complete "%s" = total elapsed seconds "%S" = total remaining seconds "%m" = total elapsed minutes "%M" = total remaining minutes "%h" = total elapsed hours "%H" = total remaining hours "%t" = total elapsed time in HH:MM:SS "%T" = total remaining time in HH:MM:SS "%f" = frame number "%%" = % character
.RE

.B --endofframe
.RS
Override the "endofframe" option from the input RIB file(s).
.RE

.B --nostandard
.RS
Disable automatic declaration of standard RenderMan parameters.
.RE

.B -v, --verbose=[level]
.RS
Controls the verbosity of output messages.  "0" = errors only.  "1" = errors and warnings (default).  "2" = errors, warnings, and information.  "3" = errors, warnings, information, and debugging output.
.RE

.B --renderinfo
.RS
Print information about base render settings.
.RE

.B --type=[type]
.RS
Specify a display device type to use.
.RE

.B --addtype=[type]
.RS
Specify a display device type to add.
.RE

.B --mode=[mode]
.RS
Specify a display device mode to use.
.RE

.B -d, --fb
.RS
Equivalent to --type="framebuffer" --mode="rgb".
.RE

.B --crop [x1] [x2] [y1] [y2]
.RS
Specify a crop window in screen space.
.RE

.B --rc=[file]
.RS
Specify a RIB configuration file that will be parsed prior to each input RIB file (overrides the default and AQSIS_RC_PATH environment variable).
.RE

.B --shaders=[path1:path2...]
.RS
Specify the path(s) used to search for compiled shaders (overrides the default and AQSIS_SHADER_PATH environment variable).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B --archives=[path1:path2...]
.RS
Specify the path(s) used to search for archived RIB files (overrides the default and AQSIS_ARCHIVE_PATH environment variable).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B --textures=[path1:path2...]
.RS
Specify the path(s) used to search for texture files (overrides the default and AQSIS_TEXTURE_PATH environment variable).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B --displays=[path1:path2...]
.RS
Specify the path(s) used to search for display plugins (overrides the default and AQSIS_DISPLAY_PATH environment variable).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B --procedurals=[path1:path2...]
.RS
Specify the path(s) used to search for procedural geometry plugins (overrides the default and AQSIS_PROCEDURAL_PATH environment variable).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B -nc, --nocolor
.RS
Disable colored log output.
.RE

.B --syslog
.RS
Log output messages to syslog (Posix only).
.RE

.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES

.B AQSIS_RC_PATH
.RS
Overrides the RIB configuration file that will be loaded prior to each input RIB file (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --rc option, above).
.RE

.B AQSIS_SHADER_PATH
.RS
Overrides the path(s) used to search for compiled shaders (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --shaders option, above).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B AQSIS_ARCHIVE_PATH
.RS
Overrides the path(s) used to search for archived RIB files (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --archives option, above).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B AQSIS_TEXTURE_PATH
.RS
Overrides the path(s) used to search for texture files (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --textures option, above).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B AQSIS_DISPLAY_PATH
.RS
Overrides the path(s) used to search for display plugins (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --displays option, above).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

.B AQSIS_PROCEDURAL_PATH
.RS
Overrides the path(s) used to search for procedural geometry plugins (this overrides the default, but can be overridden by the --procedural option, above).  You may specify multiple search paths, delimited using a colon.
.RE

